data.current_description: Returns a list of transactions for an account holder's accounts. You can specify the accounts and transaction statuses to be included on the list. The call returns a maximum of 50 transactions for each account. To retrieve all transactions, you must make another call with the 'page' value incremented. Transactions are listed in chronological order, with the most recent transaction first.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve paginated transaction list for account holder
data.description_suggestion: Returns a paginated list of transactions for an account holder's accounts. Supports filtering by specific accounts and transaction statuses. Each response returns a maximum of 50 transactions per account; use the 'page' parameter to retrieve additional transactions. Transactions are sorted in reverse chronological order (most recent first). Requires AccountHolderTransactionListRequest with account and status filters.
data.reasoning: Original summary is too generic. Description lacks clarity about pagination mechanism and input requirements. Enhanced version specifies pagination behavior, filtering capabilities, and required request parameters to improve AI agent understanding of how to use this operation iteratively.

data.current_description:
Sends a direct debit request to an account holder's bank account. If the direct debit is successful, the funds are settled in the accounts specified in the split instructions. Adyen sends the result of the direct debit in a [`DIRECT_DEBIT_INITIATED`](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/#/NotificationService/latest/post/DIRECT_DEBIT_INITIATED) notification webhook.

 To learn more about direct debits, see [Top up accounts](https://docs.adyen.com/classic-platforms/top-up-accounts).
data.description_suggestion: Initiates a direct debit request from an account holder's bank account to fund platform accounts. Upon successful processing, funds are distributed to accounts according to the specified split instructions. The operation is asynchronous; Adyen sends the result via a DIRECT_DEBIT_INITIATED webhook notification. This operation is used for top-up account funding. Note: split instructions determine how funds are allocated across multiple accounts.
data.reasoning: Summary is appropriate. Description needs clarification about asynchronous nature, webhook notification mechanism, and the role of split instructions for AI agents to understand the operation's full lifecycle and side effects.

data.current_summary: Designate a beneficiary account and transfer the benefactor's current balance
data.current_description: Defines a benefactor and a beneficiary relationship between two accounts. At the time of benefactor/beneficiary setup, the funds in the benefactor account are transferred to the beneficiary account, and any further payments to the benefactor account are automatically sent to the beneficiary account. A series of benefactor/beneficiaries may not exceed four beneficiaries and may not have a cycle in it.
data.description_suggestion: Establishes a benefactor-beneficiary relationship between two accounts on the platform. Upon setup, the current balance in the benefactor account is immediately transferred to the beneficiary account. Subsequently, all incoming payments to the benefactor account are automatically forwarded to the beneficiary account. Constraints: a benefactor chain may not exceed four beneficiaries in sequence, and circular relationships are not permitted. Requires both account identifiers and validates relationship constraints.
data.reasoning: Summary is clear and specific. Description needs clarification about immediate balance transfer (side effect), automatic forwarding mechanism, and constraint validation. Enhanced version specifies the operational flow, constraints, and required inputs for AI agents to understand when and how to use this operation safely.
